title: For Trade:  Egyptian Hakim 8mm Battle Rifle
postcontent:
I have an Hakim 8mm semi-auto battle rifle I might be interested in trading for the right offer.

Internals/metal are in excellent shape. Bolt functions like it should, and there has been no cutting or bubba type shenanigans anywhere. This gun is stock.
The wood has some dings in it, but they're minor and could be cleaned up if someone was so inclined. I didn't want to alter this rifle in any way, so I haven't tried.

These were made in the 50's and 60's by Egypt using machines that originally made the Swedish AG-42, which is similar in action but a different caliber.
These rifles were some of the first direct impingement battle rifles. Only 70,000 or so were ever made, and of that only a couple thousand were imported into the US. They have an adjustable gas system, excellent muzzle break system, and are fed by 10 round detachable box magazines.

Bore is probably good to very good, and crown is perfect. This rifle hasn't been shot in years, but it functioned flawlessly using yugo fmj ammo. It doesn't do so well with soft points.

Any other questions, just ask.

title: For Sale:  Custom AK47 - Pic Rail - 6 Mags - 400+ rounds Ammo
postcontent:
Have a very custom AK47 in 7.62x39 for sale. It is a WASR-10, but an earlier import before they started sucking. Sights are aligned, almost no trigger slap, all mags seat and feed very well. Trigger feels great, so much better then the newer ones. It features a nickle boron finish all around, inside and out. This is more corrosion resistant then the standard finish, and also creates less friction making the gun run a little better. Great for shooting corrosive ammo, so much easier to clean with this finish. Wood has been died black. US Palm grip was also added. Muzzle brake is genuine Bulgarian AK74 brake, NOT fake American versions that don't work. Muzzle is threaded, brake not pressed or pinned on.

Also included (but not pictured) is a top rail that fits over the dust cover. It replaces the rear sight, and mounts over the dust cover to the rear of the receiver. It holds zero perfect, and includes a rear peep sight similar to AR15. Rail hinges on stock rear sight mount to flip up and out of the way of the dust cover when you want to remove it. Perfect for mounting any optics, it's not as high up as the side rail mounts, so you can still get a good cheekweld with it. If using a micro red dot (like Aimpoint Micro) you can cowitness with the irons.

I also have 6 steel surplus 30 round magazines, and 400 rounds of ammo, some loose, some loaded in mags, some still sealed in boxes. All Yugo surplus, brass cased. Good stuff.

This is a real slick shooter, would like to keep it but have another project to fund. Sling pictured is not included.

$750 FTF in or around Dearborn Heights.
